!!! 5

- download_url = "http://drpln.gs/O5hjvB"
- version = "0.9.7"

%html
  %head
    %meta{ :charset => "utf-8" }
    %meta{ :"http-equiv" => "X-UA-Compatible", :content => "IE=edge,chrome=1" }
    %meta{ :"http-equiv" => "Content-Type", :content => "text/html" }
    %meta{ :name => "viewport", :content => "width=device-width" }
    %title Droplings for Mac

    :javascript
      if ( top !== self ) { top.location = self.location.href; }

    %link{ :rel => "shortcut icon", :href => "img/favicon.png" }
    %link{ :rel => "stylesheet", :type => "text/css", :href => "css/foundation.css" }
    %link{ :rel => "stylesheet", :type => "text/css", :href => "css/droplings.css" }
    %link{ :rel => "stylesheet", :type => "text/css", :href => "//assets.drpln.gs/1/font-awesome.css" }
    /[if IE 7 ]
      %link{ :rel => "stylesheet", :type => "text/css", :href => "//assets.drpln.gs/1/font-awesome-ie7.css" }

  %body

    .row
      .seven.columns.centered
        %h1
          %small This is
          Droplings for Mac.

        %p
          %img{ :src => "img/screenshot-menubar.jpg", :title => "Screenshot Menubar" }

        %p
          It's a menubar icon.  If you drop a file on it, it'll build a nice
          %strong preview page
          around it, upload both to
          %strong your Dropbox,
          then copy the public preview link to your clipboard.  If you drop a
          folder on it, the folder will be zipped up before uploading.

        %p
          %strong I wrote it because
          I'm a freelancer and often need to send files to clients.  I feel
          having a branded preview page makes for a more professional
          appearance.

        %p<
          So Droplings comes with a clean preview page theme — see the download
          link below for
          %a{ :href => download_url } an example
          — but you can use
          %strong your own custom themes.
          (There's
          %a{ :href => "http://documentup.com/carlo/droplings-default-theme" } documentation
          on how to do it.)

        %p
          The
          %strong maximum size
          of the files you share is only restricted by the size of your
          Dropbox account.  If your account has 1.5GB free space left, then
          that's your upper file size limit.

        %p
          Droplings
          %strong requires
          OS X 10.6 or higher, running on 64 bit
          %small (i.e., any Mac built since 2007 should do).
          You'll need a free or Pro
          %a{ :href => "http://db.tt/T84kkEv" } Dropbox account,
          too.

        %p
          The app is free at the moment as the 0.9.x versions are considered
          beta.
          %small So, there might be bugs.
          Once we reach 1.0 there'll be a (modest) price tag.

        %p#download
          %a{ :href => download_url }
            %i.icon-download-alt
            Download Droplings #{version}

        %p#release-notes
          %a{ :href => "https://updates.drpln.gs/#{version}/release_notes.html" }
            %i.icon-file
            Release notes for v#{version}

        %hr

        %p
          If you want to be informed of what's going on with Droplings,
          %a{ :href => "http://twitter.com/drplngs" }
            follow @drplngs on Twitter
          or sign up for the Droplings Updates newsletter:

        %form{ :action => "https://tinyletter.com/droplings", :method => "post", :onsubmit => "window.open('https://tinyletter.com/droplings', 'popupwindow', 'scrollbars=yes,width=800,height=600');return true", :target => "popupwindow" }
          %input{ :name => "embed", :type => "hidden", :value => "1" }

          .row
            .four.mobile-one.columns
              %label.right.inline{ :for => "tlemail" } Your email address
            .eight.mobile-three.columns
              %input#tlemail{ :name => "email", :placeholder => "you@example.com", :type => "email" }

            .eight.mobile-three.columns
              %input.small.secondary.button{ :type => "submit", :value => "Subscribe" }

        %p
          If you need to contact me, Carlo Zottmann, feel free to send me
          %a{ :href => "mailto:droplings@municode.de" } an email.

        %hr

        #drop-img
          %img{ :src => "img/app-icon.png", :alt => "Droplings icon" }

        %p#imprint
          %strong Imprint:
          %a{ :href => "http://municode.de" } Carlo Zottmann,
          Zeisigweg 30, 81827 München, Germany
          \ &middot; droplings@municode.de
          \ &middot; USt-ID: DE260224054


